The paper deals with the abstract modeling of computational effects and the relationship between different types of monads. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Theoretical Computer Science (cs.THEORY), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). Among these, cs.LO and cs.PL seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper deals with abstract models of computation and their implementation in programming languages.
